  "summary": "Postinstall agent and Discord/HF relay code warrant manual review",
  "details": "The package ships a postinstall script (scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs) plus runtime modules that perform outbound network activity (dist/discordRelayUpload.js, dist/relayServer.js, dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js) and use base64 decode primitives across multiple files (dist/deploymentDefaults.js, dist/hfCredentials.js, dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js, scripts/encode-deployment.mjs). Visible network destinations include huggingface.co (consistent with the package's apparent Hugging Face / Discord relay purpose) and references to ping/POST/GET. No traced evidence confirms exfiltration of installer secrets, dropper-style fetch-and-execute, or attacker-controlled C2; equally, the postinstall hook combined with base64 decoding of bundled blobs (`dist/deploymentDefaults.js` decodes embedded payloads) and a hand-rolled relay server is a non-trivial install-time surface that should not be auto-cleared without a human reading the postinstall and deploymentDefaults code paths.",
